ephritis and to seek medical attention if they occur, including edema, shortness of breath, coughing, hematuria, and decreased urination.', 'Excretion', 'Caution is advised when inotersen is prescribed with nephrotoxic drugs and other drugs that may impair renal function (e.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/24552/', '[1] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[2] "Product Information. Tegsedi (inotersen)." Akcea Therapeutics, Cambridge, MA.', 'Tamsulosin, Tinidazole, Ascorbic acid, Hydroflumethiazide, Chlorothiazide, Metronidazole, Simeprevir, Rosuvastatin, Sulfadiazine, Lactic acid, Mitapivat, More', 'Dextromethorphan, Valbenazine, Dalfampridine, Sodium oxybate, Riluzole, Tetrabenazine, Pitolisant, Amifampridine, Deutetrabenazine, Tafamidis', 1767369485);
